<!-- 
As Summer
into Autumn
slips

And yet
we sooner
say
"The Summer" than "the Autumn", lest
We turn the
Sun away,

And almost
count it an
Affront the
presence to
concede
Of one however
lovely, not
The one
that we have
loved -

So we evade
the Charge
of Years
One one On one attempting shy
The Circumvention
of the Shaft
Of Life's
declivity.
-->
